  <h2>Locations Across Livingston County</h2>

  <h3>Howell</h3>
  <p>Downtown Howell's historic charm, Thompson Lake's golden hour light, and the trails near the Howell Nature Center make this my home base for family sessions. The variety within a few miles is incredible.</p>

  <h3>Brighton</h3>
  <p>Kensington Metropark, Huron Meadows, Brighton Mill Pond, and Island Lake Recreation Area — Brighton has some of the best parks in Southeast Michigan for family photos. The mature trees and open meadows photograph beautifully in every season.</p>

  <h3>Hartland</h3>
  <p>Parshallville's historic cider mill area, the rolling countryside, and local farms give Hartland sessions a rural charm that's hard to find anywhere else. If your family has property in the area, shooting on your own land makes the photos even more meaningful.</p>

  <h3>Fowlerville, Pinckney &amp; Beyond</h3>
  <p>From the quiet rural roads of Fowlerville to the lakeside settings around Pinckney, every town in Livingston County has its own feel. I love exploring new spots — if you have a favorite place, let's shoot there.</p>

  <h2>What Your Family Session Looks Like</h2>
  <p>Every session starts with a conversation. What's your style? How old are the kids? What time of day works best? I plan everything around your family so session day is fun, not stressful.</p>

  <p>I guide you through natural prompts — walking together, playing with the kids, real interactions that bring out genuine smiles and laughter. Most sessions last about an hour, and I recommend scheduling during golden hour for the warmest, most flattering light.</p>

  <p>Your private gallery with print release is delivered within 2-3 weeks. Download, share, and order products like gallery wraps, albums, and prints.</p>

